  <name>CrossMacro</name>
  <developer_name>Alper Han</developer_name>
  <summary>Mouse Macro Automation Tool</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      CrossMacro is a modern mouse macro recording and playback tool designed for Linux Wayland compositors.
      It supports recording mouse events, playing them back with adjustable speed, and looping.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Record and replay mouse movements and clicks</li>
      <li>Support for Hyprland, KDE, and GNOME Wayland sessions</li>
      <li>Global hotkeys for control (F8: Record, F9: Play, F10: Stop)</li>
      <li>Adjustable playback speed</li>
      <li>Loop mode for continuous playback</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
